      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Utility Trailer Lights FAQs</h2><h3>What are utility trailer work lights used for?</h3><p>They provide illumination for loading, unloading, and working in dark or low-visibility conditions.</p><h3>What type of work light is best for utility trailers?</h3><p>Floodlights are great for wide coverage, while spotlights offer focused beams. Combination lights offer the best of both worlds.</p><h3>Are LED work lights better than halogen for trailers?</h3><p>Yes, LEDs are more energy-efficient, have a longer lifespan, and are more durable than halogen bulbs.</p><h3>Can I install work lights on my trailer myself?</h3><p>Yes, with basic tools and wiring knowledge, most trailer work lights are easy to install.</p><h3>Do trailer work lights need to be waterproof?</h3><p>Absolutely—look for lights with at least an IP65 rating to ensure weather resistance.</p><h3>Can work lights run off a 12V trailer battery?</h3><p>Yes, most LED work lights are designed to run off standard 12V power systems.</p><h3>Where can I buy utility trailer work lights online? </h3><p>Strobes N More offers a wide selection of high-quality trailer work lights for all applications.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
